unions.name: Error
unions.comment: Represents an error that may occur when trying to get the local zone.

values.name: getZone
values.comment:
Try to get the local time zone. If the task succeeds, then you get the zone
name along with the `Time.Zone`.

values.name: unpack
values.comment:
Convert a `TimeZone.Data.Pack` to a `Time.Zone`.

    import Time
    import TimeZone exposing (unpack)
    import TimeZone.Data

    zone : Time.Zone
    zone =
        unpack TimeZone.Data.america__new_york

name: TimeZone.Data
comment:
This module contains data from the `2018e` release of the IANA Time
Zone Database.

@docs Pack, packs


## Zones

Data for each zone is contained in a `Pack` named after its zone name (e.g.
`America/New_York`), where slashes are replaced by `__`, dashes are replaced
by `_`, and the name is lowercased. For example, `America/Port-au-Prince`
becomes `america__port_au_prince`.

@docs version, minYear, maxYear

aliases.name: Pack
aliases.comment:
Represents information required to create a `Time.Zone`. A `Pack` must be
converted to a `Time.Zone` with the `TimeZone.unpack` function.

values.name: maxYear
values.comment: How far forward does it go?

values.name: minYear
values.comment: How far back does this data go?

values.name: packs
values.comment:
You can look up a `Pack` by its zone name in the `packs` dictionary.

    import Dict
    import TimeZone.Data exposing (packs, america__new_york)

    Dict.get "America/New_York" packs

    -- Just america__new_york

values.name: version
values.comment: What version of the IANA Time Zone Database is this data from?
